COMPARISON: I(G,2) = 43 and I(G,2) = 63
==================================================

I(G,2) = 43: 60 graphs, 1 distinct polynomials
  I(G,x) = 1 + 5x + 6x^2 + x^3: NOT (1+3x)|
  → I(G,2)=43 has graphs NOT poisoned by K₃. CAN be Ω(T).

I(G,2) = 63: 70 graphs, 1 distinct polynomials
  I(G,x) = 1 + 5x + 7x^2 + 3x^3: (1+3x)|
  → ALL graphs with I(G,2)=63 are K₃-poisoned.

